net.sandius.rembulan.runtime

Class Dispatch

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sandius.rembulan.runtime.Dispatch

  • public final class Dispatch
extends Object
    A static class for dispatching operations according to the semantics of Lua 5.3.

      • call

        public static void call(ExecutionContext context,
                        Object target)
                 throws UnresolvedControlThrowable
        Calls the object target with no arguments. This method throws an UnresolvedControlThrowable: non-local control changes are expected to be resolved by the caller of this method.

        This is the equivalent of the Lua expression

             target()

        including metamethod handling and tail call evaluation. Consequently, target may be any value (i.e., is not required to be a function).

        The results of the call will be stored in the return buffer associated with context.

        Parameters:
        context - execution context, must not be null
        target - call target, may be null
        Throws:
        UnresolvedControlThrowable - if the call initiates a non-local control change
        NullPointerException - if context is null
        IllegalOperationAttemptException - if target is not a function and does not have the __call metamethod

      • call

        public static void call(ExecutionContext context,
                        Object target,
                        Object[] args)
                 throws UnresolvedControlThrowable
        Calls the object target with the arguments passed in the array args. This method throws an UnresolvedControlThrowable: non-local control changes are expected to be resolved by the caller of this method.

        This is the equivalent of the Lua expression

             target(a_0, ..., a_n)

        where a_i denotes the value of args[i] and n is equal to (args.length - 1), including metamethod handling and tail call evaluation. Consequently, target may be any value (i.e., is not required to be a function).

        Following the contract of LuaFunction.invoke(ExecutionContext, Object[]), the array args passed to the called function may not be modified by the function and the reference to args must not be retained by the function beyond the scope of this method's invocation. It is therefore safe to assume that the contents of args will be the same after this method has returned. (No need for a defensive copy.)

        The results of the call will be stored in the return buffer associated with context.

        If args is null, then the behaviour of this method is undefined.

        Parameters:
        context - execution context, must not be null
        target - call target, may be null
        args - call arguments, must not be null
        Throws:
        UnresolvedControlThrowable - if the call initiates a non-local control change
        NullPointerException - if context is null
        IllegalOperationAttemptException - if target is not a function and does not have the __call metamethod

      • signed_le

        public static boolean signed_le(Number a,
                                Number b,
                                Number sign)
        Returns true iff a op b, where op is "<=" (lesser than or equal to) if sign > 0, or ">=" (greater than or equal to) if sign < 0.

        When sign is zero or NaN, returns false.

        Parameters:
        a - the first operand, must not be null
        b - the second operand, must not be null
        sign - the sign, must not be null
        Returns:
        true iff a is below b depending on the sign of sign
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if a, b or sign is null
